Preheat the oven to 190C/375F/Gas 5.Melt the butter in a small saucepan.  Add the onions and cook them for about 6 minutes or until they are transparent. Add the herbs, breadcrumbs and seasoning, stirring well to combine everything.Spoon the stuffing into the cavities of the apples.  Place the apples into a dish, dot the top with butter and put into the oven for about 45-60 minutes. Serve as an accompaniment with pork or duck dishes.